---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Adapters" description="RankMySEO server adapters — Hono, Express, Next, Nitro, SvelteKit, Astro.">
  <h1>Server adapters</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    Prefer a thin framework adapter when one exists. SvelteKit and Astro use the framework-agnostic
    <code>createHandler</code> from <code>@rankmyseo/server</code> (native <code>Request</code> / <code>Response</code>).
  </p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Framework</th>
        <th>Package / pattern</th>
        <th>Entry</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Hono</td>
        <td><code>@rankmyseo/server-hono</code></td>
        <td><code>createRankMySeoApp(store, options)</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Express</td>
        <td><code>@rankmyseo/server-express</code></td>
        <td><code>createRankMySeoExpress(store, options)</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Next.js App Router</td>
        <td><code>@rankmyseo/server-next</code></td>
        <td><code>createRankMySeoRouteHandlers(store, options)</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Nitro / Nuxt (h3)</td>
        <td><code>@rankmyseo/server-nitro</code></td>
        <td><code>createRankMySeoNitroHandler(store, options)</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>SvelteKit</td>
        <td><code>@rankmyseo/server</code> + <code>examples/sveltekit-adapter</code></td>
        <td><code>createHandler</code> in <code>+server.ts</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Astro</td>
        <td><code>@rankmyseo/server</code> + <code>examples/astro-adapter</code></td>
        <td><code>createHandler</code> in API catch-all (Node / hybrid output)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Any Node HTTP</td>
        <td><code>@rankmyseo/server</code></td>
        <td><code>createHandler(store, options)</code></td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Runtime note</h3>
    <p>
      Mount under Node.js ≥ 20. Full-stack RankMySEO is <strong>not</strong> edge/Workers compatible.
      Use <code>basePath</code> when nesting under a subpath (e.g. <code>/api/rankmyseo</code>).
      Scope headers select tenant/project — wire <code>authorize</code> for real auth.
    </p>
  </div>

  <p>
    Related:
    <a href="https://github.com/madebyaris/rankmyseo/wiki/Architecture">Architecture</a> ·
    <a href="/demo">Client demo</a> ·
    <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@rankmyseo/client">@rankmyseo/client</a> ·
    <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@rankmyseo/collector">@rankmyseo/collector</a>
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
